cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.CY, cs.AI 

This paper uses machine learning and natural language processing techniques to classify medical literature on cancer susceptibility genes. The use of machine learning models such as support vector machines and convolutional neural networks suggests a focus on natural language processing and classification tasks, which are commonly found in the computer science sub-categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves information retrieval (cs.IR) techniques for literature searches and classification, as well as potential applications in clinical decision support tools (cs.CY) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
